<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-11T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60 f 12A/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-11T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 11,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:25
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>54. Your 28, June 28 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], 5 p.m. Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs tells me that he is instructing Czechoslovak Minister in
                            Washington to sign arbitration treaty in the form desired by you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>